== -t keyword:
keyword
== -t builtin:
builtin
== -t alias:
alias
== -t function:
function
== -t conditional bracket keyword:
keyword
== default keyword spelling:
for is a shell keyword
== default builtin spelling:
echo is a shell builtin
== default alias spelling:
g is an alias for git
== default function spelling:
f is a shell function
== -a lists a keyword with no file:
for is a shell keyword
== -p stays silent for a builtin:
rc=0
== -t stays silent for a missing name:
rc=1
== a missing name reports not found:
missing_xyz: not found
rc=1
